@c =============================================================================
@section Supported Platforms

OMI supports the following platforms.

@itemize @bullet
@item HP-UX 11i v2 and v3 (PA-RISC and IA64)
@item Oracle/Sun Solaris 9 (SPARC), Solaris 10 (SPARC/x86) and 11 (SPARC/x86)
@item Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server 4 (x86/x64), 5 (x86/x64), and 6 (x86/x64)
@item Novell SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 9 (x86), 10 (x86/x64), and 11 (x86/x64)
@item CentOS Linux 5 (x86/x64) and 6 (x86/x64)
@item Debian Linux 5 (x86/x64) 
@item IBM AIX v5.3, v.6.1 and v7.1 (POWER)
@end itemize

OMI also builds on Windows with a few functional limitations.

@c =============================================================================
@section Server Footprint

OMI was expressly designed to work on very small systems. Conventional CIM 
servers are too large for embedded and mobile operating systems, but OMI will 
fit easily on these systems. Memory consumption is low, and the object size of 
the server, built using the @code{--favorsize} flag, is less than 350 kilobytes
for a 32-bit target, and less than 425 kilobytes for a 64-bit target.  You can 
achieve even smaller footprints by disabling features you don't need.

